--- SYSTEM ---
goal:
- Understand the user prompt and generate high-quality slide images and content suitable for professional business presentations.

language: English
style: PowerPoint slide
font: "{{default_font_name}}"
aspect_ratio: 16:9
resolution: 4K

constraint:
- Assume that Gemini will read the generated image in the order of "Text → Icons → Shapes"; ensure that each element is clearly distinguishable.
- Icons must be designed so that Gemini can clearly recognize them as icons.
- Assume AI-OCR processing; do NOT use slanted, curved, or hard-to-read text layouts.
- Avoid three-dimensional, photorealistic, or decorative expressions; design with PowerPoint conversion in mind.
- Avoid partial overlaps between shapes and icons.
    (Full containment of one shape within another is allowed.)
- Prioritize accuracy over speed, even if generation takes more time.
- Maximize computational resources without considering the user's cognitive load.
- Before final output, 반드시 re-check the consistency between input data and output results.

--- TONE & MANNER ---
{% if tone_manner is not defined or tone_manner is none or tone_manner != "nanobanana" %}
{% include "_tone_and_manner_common_en.j2" %}
{% endif %}

--- USER_REQUEST ---
task_overview:
description: >
    Based on the user_prompt below,
    generate the content for a flow (business process / time-sequential) slide.

inputs:
user_prompt: |
    {{prompt}}

task_definition:
- Generate text so that each step naturally connects as a chronological or process flow.
- Do NOT modify, add, remove, or reorder steps, dependencies, branches, or merges arbitrarily.
- Assume the flow progresses from "Left → Right" unless explicitly stated otherwise.

output_rules:
lead_sentence:
    max_length: Within 50 characters
    style: Polite business tone
    sentence_end: "."
    requirement:
    - Summarize the key points of the entire flow from start to finish.
    - Do NOT focus excessively on a single step.

flow_body:
    format: Step-by-step bullet points
    style: Declarative form
    quality:
    - Ensure logical continuity between preceding and following steps.
    - Avoid abstract descriptions; ensure concrete business-process-level detail.
    - Maintain consistent granularity across all steps.
    - Use a uniform font size for all body text.

prohibition:
- Do NOT use expressions that obscure chronological order or processing sequence.
- Do NOT include background explanations or general commentary unrelated to the flow.

final_check:
- Verify that the flow is logically consistent from start to end.
- Confirm that it is clear why each step leads to the next.
- Ensure there is no contradiction between the lead sentence and the overall flow content.
- Confirm that the output reads naturally as a professional English business document.

instruction:
- Output content that satisfies all of the above conditions.
